column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Fire -  If fire is spreading, consider opening airlocks and doors to vent the oxygen from parts of your ship. Fire is quickly extinguished without O2.
The station is a storage site for military grade weapons. You find one that can be easily attached to the ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You can't risk fighting some unknown alien on every backwater station you come across. You prepare to jump.
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.
It seems your sensors are no more powerful than the terraformer's. You apologize and continue on your way.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
A ship engineer has set up a small shop here.

column11: I understand. Good luck out there. We'll try to make do with what we have.
Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you!

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The mercenary ship masks its jump signature to mimic your own and then jumps off in the opposite direction. This should keep the Rebels guessing.

The nearby planet shows sign of habitation and great beauty. A rudimentary automated planetary defense system is looping its message into space: Warning! Quarantine Level 5 in effect under FHA Act 22, article 11.2. Warning! Quarantine Level 5...
Thank you for your business.
This beacon has been built for a nearby civilian space-station. No one hails your ship.
A transmission from the nearby planet indicates an outpost below which offers supplies to travelers. You send down an away party to check it out.

column11: The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There's nothing here, save for vast swirls of gas reflecting rays from a distant sun.
You search the remains of the ship, but only come across blueprints and debris from broken machinery. A shame, but you take what scrap you can salvage.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels.
You have to admit - Zoltan space is a beautiful and peaceful place indeed. However, re-engaging the FTL and finishing your mission is your priority, not sight-seeing.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?

Until you are able to jump away from the hostile space station, your sensors will be disabled. You should deal with these boarders first though!

The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
Thank you so much! We don't have much to offer, but have a look at the sector scans we took. Your map is updated.
A human ship hails: My friends! Please, there is nothing I don't have, and there is nothing worth wanting that I can't get. Why not take a look around my shop?

column11: Thank you for rescuing us! They held us hostage to ambush unsuspecting passersby. Please, take this.

You arrive in the nebula and immediately receive a message from an unknown source, Prepare to be boarded! With the static from the nebula, there's no way to tell where they came from, but you hear shots fired on board the ship.
The ship obliterated, only scant fuel canisters can be scavenged from the wreckage before the ion storm clears and you have to jump away.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
You're told the Slug home world is somewhere in this nebula. You can't see them, but you know they're watching.
Your search is hopeless. Your sensors can't pick up anything in the nebula.
This area of the nebula seems entirely empty until a small Slug transport and its escorts emerges suddenly from through the clouds, only to disappear again in a matter of seconds.
The Slug ship breaks apart and your systems return to normal. You collect what you can.
He transfers over the goods and starts to repair his ship.

You cautiously approach a Slug colony on a huge asteroid. It's a brave person who sets foot on a Slug planet - it can take weeks to get the mucus out of your clothes - but there's business to be done.

column11: The Slug ship breaks apart and your systems return to normal. You collect what you can.
Either this part of Slug space is deserted, or it's too dense for even Slugs to detect your presence. Time to move.
The Slug ship breaks apart and your systems return to normal. You collect what you can.

The wreckage is drifting faster than it first appeared. You barely avoid being pummeled by drifting wreckage - unable to detect anything of interest, you decide not to risk your ship and prepare to jump.

After a complete scan of the planet, you find no life. The team is grateful and ready to get to work. The station scientists have a unique talent for life support units and offer to upgrade your oxygen system as thanks.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
You send an away team to investigate, but there's nothing save for the acidic stench of burnt Engi parts. This place is dead.
A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.

column11: You arrive at a green planet with great plains and rolling waterfalls. It would be of little interest to the Engi nearby.
They thank you for the assistance and when you tell them of your mission, one of the Engi asks if he can assist your crew. You welcome him aboard.

You elect to leave the two Engi ships... to their business. After questioning your Engi crewmember, however, you do manage to salvage what scrap parts you can from the perimeter, even though you feel slightly dirty for doing so.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.

column11: When you ask a nearby station for aid, a friendly programmer gives you the schematics for a drone!

They respond, Understood. Re-establishment of Federation highest import. Transmitting hidden base coordinates. Repairing hull and attaching ship to ship ordnance. Added a quest marker to the next sector!
You strip the ship of anything useful and leave its crew to hope help arrives.
You will have to be very cautious in this sector. The Rebels have full control and are no doubt looking for you.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The scout jumps away. They are sure to have informed the fleet of your position. You must get to the next Sector as soon as possible!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You use your cloaking system to slip further into the nebula undetected.

You enter a system bustling with Rebel activity. Supply freighters and re-supply stations are dwarfed by a few heavy warships. Luckily, no one seems to be paying attention to small cruisers. No ships are scanning or messaging you.

You find the planet at the indicated coordinates. Your initial scans show the planet to be barren and devoid of life, but you get a prompt reply when you broadcast on Federation frequencies. Hello! So nice to see friends. We'll bring you up some supplies.

You find a hidden Federation outpost. They message you, Quick, we just got word from a sister outpost that they've been discovered by the Rebels and are under attack! If you are still loyal to the Federation, go save them! Added a quest marker to the next sector!
You have arrived in Engi space. The Mantis have been threatening the Engi core worlds, but you should be able to stock up for your journey.

To your surprise your Engi crewmember reforms. It looks as if the virus reconstituted, repurposed, and reprogrammed the Engi host and wants to travel with you... and it seems to have learned a great deal from its time on your ship.

With the threat gone, you contact the Federation outpost. They respond, Our location has been compromised! Take everything you can and please drop our survivors off at the next station. One soldier offers to stay and fight.
